============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   ATP
Formula: ADP + Pi → ATP
Note:    Universal energy currency of all living cells

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Ohm's Law
Formula: V = IR
Note:    Voltage, current, resistance relationship in circuits

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Central Limit Theorem
Formula: Sample means → normal distribution
Note:    Foundation of statistical inference and polling

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Bayes Theorem
Formula: P(A|B) = P(B|A)P(A)/P(B)
Note:    Updating probability based on new evidence

Domain:  Medicine
Topic:   Germ Theory
Formula: Microorganisms cause disease
Note:    Pasteur/Koch; foundation of modern medicine

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

Concept:    GDP
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Total value of all goods and services produced in a country annually
Formula:    GDP = C + I + G + (X-M)
Economist:  Simon Kuznets
Example:    USA GDP 2023: $27.4 trillion; China: $17.9 trillion

Concept:    Inflation
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: General rise in price levels eroding purchasing power
Formula:    Inflation = (CPI_t - CPI_t-1)/CPI_t-1 x 100
Economist:  Irving Fisher
Example:    2022 US inflation hit 9.1%; Fed raised rates to combat it

